text: Tricondyloides inermis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae. It was described by Stephan von Breuning in 1939.BioLib.cz - Tricondyloides inermis. Retrieved on 8 September 2014. It is 4.5 mm long and 1.75 mm wide, and its type locality is Mont Panié, New Caledonia. ==References== Category:Lamiinae Category:Beetles described in 1939 Category:Taxa named by Stephan von Breuning
title: Tricondyloides inermis
